.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Crytwi Python version or libcrytwi provides several APIs to transform raw data streams and create a Crytwi format file. It facilitates the creation of encrypted volumes and supports random-access decryption, allowing users to verify and retrieve data from existing Crytwi files with minimal memory overhead.
.PP
libcrytwi implements a self-describing binary format with headers and deterministic chunking, enabling fast random access to encrypted data without external database dependencies.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Practical implementation examples are shipped with the library. For isolated mode command-line interface usage, refer to:
.IP
.I src/crytwi/cli.py
.PP
in source directory or tarball,
.IP
.I /usr/lib/python3/dist-packages/crytwi/cli.py
.PP
if this library installed by package manager.
.PP
Simple verification scripts for manual testing of encryption and decryption routines are located in source directory or tarball:
.IP
.I tests/
.PP
These scripts serve as a basic reference for integrating the library functions into a standard workflow.
.SH ATTENTIONS
.PP
To utilize \fBArgon2id\fR features, a modern cryptographic environment is required \fB(OpenSSL >= 3.2 and Python Cryptography >= 44.0)\fR. Initialization will fail on legacy systems that do not meet these minimum version requirements.
